25|$|Evangelicals {{maintain}} a Reformed view of Holy Communion, believing that Christ is spiritually {{present in the}} Eucharist, rather than corporeally present. <b>According</b> <b>to</b> <b>this</b> <b>view,</b> known as receptionism, the body and blood of Christ are received spiritually by faith.|$|E
