25|$|The Harmonites {{tended to}} view {{unmarried}} celibate life as morally superior to marriage, based on Rapp's belief that God had originally created Adam as a dual being, having {{male and female}} sexual organs. <b>According</b> <b>to</b> <b>this</b> <b>view,</b> when the female portion of Adam separated to form Eve, disharmony followed, but one could attempt to regain harmony through celibacy.|$|E
